This paper deals with achieving consensus in a distributed system, which is a core topic in Distributed Computing (cs.DC). The communication model used in the paper is motivated by wireless networks, which falls under the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves analyzing the underlying communication graph, which is a common theme in the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The problem of achieving consensus is also relevant to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY), as it involves controlling the behavior of a distributed system. Finally, the paper involves analyzing the reliability of message transmission, which is a topic in Information Theory (cs.IT).
